data.enText: including all, or almost all, the items, details, facts, information, etc., that may be concerned
data.chText: 全部的；所有的；（几乎）无所不包的；详尽的

data.enText: designed for students of all abilities in the same school
data.chText: 综合性的（接收各种资质的学生）

data.enText: (in Britain) a secondary school for young people of all levels of ability
data.chText: （英国为各种资质的学生设立的）综合中学

simple_means.memory_skill: com- 共同, 一起 + prehend 抓, 抓住 + -ive 形容词后缀

means: 综合性的(接收各种资质的学生)
(英国为各种资质的学生设立的)综合中学

tr: an intensive examination testing a student's proficiency in some special field of knowledge
example: she took her comps in English literature
a comprehensive history of the revolution
a comprehensive survey of world affairs

example.ex: The Rough Guide to Nepal is a comprehensive guide to the region.
example.tran: 《尼泊尔概况》是一本全面介绍该地区的旅游指南。

value.def: Something that is comprehensive includes everything that is needed or relevant.

example.tran: 伯明翰旧城区的综合中学

example.ex: She taught French at Cheam Comprehensive in South London.
example.tran: 她在伦敦南部的奇姆综合中学教法语。

example.ex: He left comprehensive school at the age of 16.
example.tran: 他16岁就从综合中学毕业了。

value.def: In Britain, a comprehensive is a state school in which children of all abilities are taught together.

trans: 良好的个人综合素质；综合素质；综合品质；全面素质
综合治理；综合治疗；综合处理
综合性大学；综合大学；四年制大学；四年制综合性大学；综合研究型大学
综合英语；综合英语课程
